ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.309                Enzyme
NAME        phosphonoacetaldehyde reductase (NADH);
            PhpC
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     2-hydroxyethylphosphonate:NAD+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    2-hydroxyethylphosphonate + NAD+ = phosphonoacetaldehyde + NADH + H+ [RN:R09478]
ALL_REAC    R09478
SUBSTRATE   2-hydroxyethylphosphonate [CPD:C06451];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003]
PRODUCT     phosphonoacetaldehyde [CPD:C03167];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The enzyme from Streptomyces viridochromogenes catalyses a step in the biosynthesis of phosphinothricin tripeptide, the reduction of phosphonoacetaldehyde to 2-hydroxyethylphosphonate. The preferred cofactor is NADH, lower activity with NADPH [1].
HISTORY     EC 1.1.1.309 created 2011
